OL,3,CLiverpool falls silent to mark 35
OL,4,Cyears since Hillsborough disaster
OL,6,FMembers of the public were invited to
OL,7,Fgather at Exchange Flags for the
OL,8,Fsilence, led by the Lord Mayor of
OL,9,FLiverpool Mary Rasmussen.
OL,11,FFlags were flown at half mast on civic
OL,12,Fbuildings and football club sites
OL,13,Fthroughout the day.JSir Kenny
OL,14,FDalglish, Liverpool's manager at the
OL,15,Ftime of the tragedy, and the club's
OL,16,Fcurrent manager Jurgen Klopp were
OL,17,Famong club officials who laid flowers
OL,18,Fat Anfield stadium's Hillsborough
OL,19,Fmemorial on Monday morning.
