OL,3,CLiverpool falls silent to mark 35
OL,4,Cyears since Hillsborough disaster
OL,6,FNinety-seven balloons were released at
OL,7,FAnfield in memory of those who lost
OL,8,Ftheir lives.
OL,10,FThe Mersey ferry sounded its horn at
OL,11,Fthe beginning and end of the minute's
OL,12,Fsilence and traffic was held through
OL,13,Fthe Mersey Tunnels.
OL,15,FLabour leader Sir Keir Starmer re-
OL,16,Faffirmed his commitment to a
OL,17,FHillsborough Law which campaigners are
OL,18,Fcalling for to help victims of other
OL,19,Fscandals to get justice.
